The Micro Combined Heat and Power (CHP) market is segmented based on technology, capacity, and application. In terms of technology, the market is divided into internal combustion engines, fuel cells, Stirling engines, and others. Internal combustion engines remain a popular choice due to their reliability and cost-effectiveness. Fuel cells are gaining traction for their efficiency and environmentally friendly operation. Stirling engines are also emerging in the market for their low emissions and quiet operation. The capacity segment includes systems up to 5kW, between 5kW to 10kW, and above 10kW, catering to a wide range of customer needs. Residential, commercial, and industrial applications constitute the market segments based on application. The residential segment is witnessing significant growth due to the increasing focus on energy-efficient solutions for homes. The commercial and industrial sectors are adopting micro CHP systems to reduce energy costs and carbon footprints.

